author: Inside Edition
description: Nikki Glaser rolled out the red carpet at the Beverly Hilton for Sunday's Golden Globes. The pressure is on as the comedian gears up to host the show for the second year in a row. "We're gonna laugh at the celebrities that can take it ... and completely ignore the ones who can't. I'm just kidding, they're not safe either," Glaser tells Inside Edition's Jim Moret. She tells Moret that she may have nine wardrobe changes like last year.
title: Nikki Glaser Gears Up To Host Golden Globes For 2nd Year In A Row

author: Inside Edition
description: The 37-year-old woman shot and killed by an ICE agent has been identified as Renee Good. She was a mom of three children. Last year, Good moved from Kansas City to Minneapolis to start a new life with a woman named Becca who she had fallen in love with. The two started their own home repair business. Good's wife was with her during the encounter with ICE agents that ended in tragedy. Good was an award-winning poet, and her mother called her "one of the kindest people I've ever known."
title: Woman Killed By ICE Agent Identified As 37-Year-Old Renee Good

author: Inside Edition
description: Chaos on the streets of Minneapolis Thursday following the shooting death of 37-year-old mom Renee Good by an ICE agent. Debate over the shooting continues to rage across the country. President Donald Trump claimed the woman "viciously ran over the ICE officer, who seems to have shot her in self-defense." In video of the incident, as the agent approached Good's car window, she reversed and accelerated away from the agent. She was shot three times. The agent who fired did not appear to be injured.
title: Protests Across The Country After Woman Killed By ICE Agent

author: Inside Edition
description: Dry January has become so popular, it has generated new businesses dedicated to drinkers who want a delicious mocktail. Kacie McIntosh, a contestant on the hit reality show "Love Is Blind," is on week one of Dry January and says she feels more energized than ever. Bars are also answering the demand. At Dear Irving, a bar in Manhattan, bartender director Meghan Dorman showed Inside her popular non-alcoholic espresso martini.
title: Some Businesses Accommodating Popularity of 'Dry January'

description: Why is this lollipop being featured at the Consumer Electronics Show? Those willing to try it out got an unusual surprise.
